This paper deals with the development of social skills in robots through reinforcement learning. The paper focuses on the interaction between humans and robots, which falls under the category of Human-Computer Interaction (HCI). The use of reinforcement learning and predictive models suggests that the paper may also belong to the categories of Robotics (cs.RO), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Machine Learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of computer vision techniques to gather data, which suggests that it may also belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) category.
